This document provides a step-by-step list to remind gcalctool
maintainers how to make a release. 

(It's been shamelessly copied and modified, based on a similar
document created for Orca by Will Walker - thanks!)

Note that this shows the steps for releasing gcalctool v5.21.4. 
Adjust as necessary for other releases.

The general instructions for a release are here:

  http://developer.gnome.org/dotplan/for_maintainers.html

Here's a summary for gcalctool:

PREPARE SOURCES FOR THE RELEASE:
-------------------------------

Modify this line in ./configure.in:

AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE(gcalctool, 5.21.4)

Modify ./README to make sure it has the right Orca version.

Update ./NEWS based upon entries in ./ChangeLog

NOTE: You should also make sure the external dependencies in
configure.in are accurate.


BUILD THE RELEASE:
-----------------

$ ./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ make dist


TEST THE CANDIDATE:
------------------

cd /tmp
gunzip -c gcalctool-5.21.4.tar.gz | tar xvf -
cd gcalctool-5.21.4
./configure --prefix=/usr
make
sudo make install
gcalctool


TAG THE RELEASE:
---------------

While in the trunk directory:

svn commit
svn cp . svn+ssh://svn.gnome.org/svn/gcalctool/tags/GCALCTOOL_5_21_4


UPLOAD THE RELEASE:
------------------

scp gcalctool-5.21.4.tar.gz gnome.org:
ssh gnome.org
install-module gcalctool-5.21.4.tar.gz


ANNOUNCE THE RELEASE
--------------------

See the email sent to gnome-announce-list@gnome.org

http://mail.gnome.org/archives/gnome-announce-list/2007-December/msg00036.html
